The Chronicle Prosper Ndlovu in Victoria Falls PRESIDENT Mnangagwa has officially opened the 2022 Annual Chamber of Mines of Zimbabwe Conference here where he has challenged players in the sector to scale up production with a focus on value addition and beneficiation to contribute more to the economy. <img class="wp-image-614368 size-large" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/Chamber-of-Mines-Conference-2-680x380.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/Chamber-of-Mines-Conference-2.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/Chamber-of-Mines-Conference-2-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> President Mnangagwa at the Zimbabwe Chamber of Mines annual conference Addressing local and international mining industry executives and key service providers attending the conference today, he implored the mines and metals sector to ride on the prevailing boom in commodity market prices and demand for steel in the construction sector, to expand their earnings. <img class="wp-image-614359 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/Chamber-of-Mines-Conference-5.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/Chamber-of-Mines-Conference-5.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/Chamber-of-Mines-Conference-5-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> CEO Botswana chamber of mines Mr C Siwawa Citing some of the significant strides recorded by the sector last year, President Mnangagwa said that growth in mining should be anchored on increased investments in new technologies, value addition and beneficiation. <img class="wp-image-614362 size-large" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/Chamber-of-Mines-Conference-4-680x380.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/Chamber-of-Mines-Conference-4.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/Chamber-of-Mines-Conference-4-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Minister of State and Provincial Affairs and Devolution for Matabeleland North Cde Richard Moyo “Gone are the days of exporting products in raw form,” he said, adding that, “value addition cannot be achieved under a business as usual attitude.” …more to follow <img class="wp-image-614356 size-large" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/Chamber-of-Mines-Conference-6-680x380.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/Chamber-of-Mines-Conference-6.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/Chamber-of-Mines-Conference-6-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Delegates at the Zimbabwe Chamber of Mines annual conference  